│  I propose augmenting the baseline with a multi-fingerprint fusion strategy and replacing LogisticRegression    │
│  with HistGradientBoostingClassifier.                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                 │
│  What to change:                                                                                                │
│  1. Expand Morgan fingerprints from 1024-bit r=2 to 2048-bit r=3                                                │
│  2. Add MACCS keys (166 pharmacophore-aware structural keys)                                                    │
│  3. Add 6 physicochemical descriptors: MolLogP, TPSA, MolWt, NumHDonors, NumHAcceptors, NumRotatableBonds       │
│  4. Replace LogisticRegression with HistGradientBoostingClassifier (max_iter=300, max_depth=6)                  │
│                                                                                                                 │
│  Why: BBB penetration correlates strongly with lipophilicity (LogP) and polar surface area (TPSA) per the       │
│  Pardridge model. Morgan FP captures local substructure but misses these global properties. MACCS keys add      │
│  expert-curated functional group detection. Gradient boosting captures nonlinear interactions that linear       │
│  models cannot.                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                 │
│  Expected improvement: 3-6 percent ROC-AUC, targeting 0.93-0.95 based on MoleculeNet benchmarks.                │
│                                                                                                                 │
